      %h2
        Open Source
      %p
        I started writing code on an Apple IIe when I was 9. We used to get magazines that had coding examples in the back written in Basic and I would sit for hours copying line-by-line, each GOTO and IF/THEN conditional. That was my first open source experience.
        Over the last decade
        %a{:href => "http://github.com/wesleyhales/"}I've worked with a few languages.
        Mostly Java, Ruby, and other related server-side frameworks, along with scripting in perl, php, and anything else required to accomplish the task at hand... I've seen a lot of shit come and go.
        As a UI developer, I consider JavaScript, CSS, and HTML as my strengths.
